        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued March 30 at 5:01PM CDT until March 30 at 5:45PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>SVRPAH

The National Weather Service in Paducah has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Eastern Jackson County in southern Illinois...

* Until 545 PM CDT.

* At 501 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Altenburg, or
13 miles west of Murphysboro, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Murphysboro, Gorham, De Soto, Carbondale, Elkville, and Hurst.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for south central
and southern Illinois.</instruction>
